 Job Description
 
As a member of the Corporate team, you will be a part of the backbone of a company that builds and brings to market artificial intelligence technologies, including natural language processing and cognitive computing. You will build best practices that will serve internal (and sometimes external) customers and business partners.
 
The Project Manager position will be responsible for the overall planning, coordination, execution, completion and evaluation of specific projects ensuring consistency with company strategy, commitments and goals.
 
Deliver projects on time and within scope and budget.
 
Plan project schedule including timelines and milestones using appropriate tools.
 
Identify and manage project dependencies and critical paths.
 
Track project milestones and deliverables.
 
Develop full-scale project plans and associated communications documents.
 
Direct and manage project development from beginning to end.
 
Define project scope, goals and deliverables that support business goals in collaboration with senior management and stakeholders.
 
Work with technical SMEs to define and document technical requirements for the project.
 
Build, develop and grow any business relationships vital to the success of the project.
 
Analyze problems and help design appropriate solutions or alternatives.
 
Estimate the resources and participants needed to achieve project goals.
 
Delegate tasks and responsibilities to appropriate personnel.
 
Develop and deliver progress reports, proposals, requirements documentation and presentations.
 
Proactively manage changes in project scope, identify potential risks and devise contingency and mitigation plans.
 
Define project success criteria and disseminate them to involved parties throughout project life cycle.
 
 Requirements: 
Bachelorâ€™s Degree or equivalent relevant work experience.
 
Minimum of five years of technical/complex project management experience.
 
Experience in project management methodology and tools.
 
Proven track record of successful project management. (Technical project management required)
 
Excellent problem solving, analytical and time management skills.
 
Excellent interpersonal and organization skills.
 
